    <bootstrap thing="wpUnarmed"></bootstrap>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stVaultKid" name="Vault Kid" description="Your healthier start to life at the hands of trained doctors and sophisticated auto-docs means you reduce the difficulty of all END tests to resist the effects of disease. In addition, your carefully-planned upbringing means you have one additional tag skill of your choice.\n\nYou may also work with the Gamemaster to determine what sort of experiment took place within your Vault. Once per quest, the GM may introduce a complication which reflects the nature of the experiment you unwittingly took part in, or introduce a complication related to your early life of isolation and confinement within the Vault. If the GM does this, you immediately regain one Luck Point." compset="OriginTrait" summary="You reduce the difficulty of all END tests to resist the effects of disease. You also  gain one additional Tag Skill of your choice." uniqueness="useronce">
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcVaultDweller"/>
    <eval phase="PreTraits" priority="1000">hero.findchild[Origin].field[orMaxTagSkills].value += 1</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stFastShot" name="Fast Shot" description="If you take a second major action in combat, and use it to make a ranged attack, the additional major action only costs 1 AP, rather than 2. You cannot benefit from the Aim minor action—you’re too impatient." compset="OriginTrait" summary="Making a Ranged attack as an additional Major Action only costs 1 AP, but you cannot benefit from the Aim minor action" uniqueness="useronce">
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcSurvivor"/>
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcTribal"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stGifted" name="Gifted" description="Choose two S.P.E.C.I.A.L. attributes and increase them by +1 each. Your maximum number of Luck points is one fewer than your Luck attribute." compset="OriginTrait" summary="You gain a +1 to two attributes, but your maximum Luck Points is 1 less than your Luck attribute." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="usrCandid1" value="component.Attribute"/>
    <fieldval field="usrCandid2" value="component.Attribute"/>
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcSurvivor"/>
    <tag group="ChooseSrc2" tag="Hero"/>
    <tag group="ChooseSrc1" tag="Hero"/>
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcTribal"/>
    <eval phase="Traits" priority="5000" index="2">~ -1 to Luck
#resmax[resLuckPoints] -= 1</eval>
    <eval phase="Setup" priority="1000"><![CDATA[~ +1 to two attributes
if (field[usrChosen1].ischosen <> 0) then
  field[usrChosen1].chosen.field[trtBonus].value += 1
  endif
if (field[usrChosen2].ischosen <> 0) then
  field[usrChosen2].chosen.field[trtBonus].value += 1
  endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stSmallFrame" name="Small Frame" description="You may re-roll 1d20 on all AGI tests which rely on balance or contortion. Your carry weight is 150 + (5 x STR) lbs., rather than 150 + (10 x STR) lbs." compset="OriginTrait" summary="You may re-roll 1d20 on all AGI tests which rely on balance or contortion, your additional carry weight is halved." uniqueness="useronce">
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcSurvivor"/>
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcTribal"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stForcedEvolution" name="Forced Evolution" description="Your initial Strength and Endurance attributes are increased by +2 each, and your maximum Strength and Endurance are increased to 12, but your maximum Intelligence and Charisma are both reduced to 6. You may not have more than 4 ranks in any skill. You are completely immune to radiation and poison damage.\n\nYou stand over seven feet tall, and your body is bulky and muscular. Your skin is green, yellow, or grey, regardless of what color it was when you were human. You do not seem to age, but you are sterile.\n\nYou can only wear armor which has been made to fit a super mutant." compset="OriginTrait">
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcSuperMutant"/>
    <eval phase="Setup" priority="1000">~ +2 Strength and Endurance (and Maximums)
#traitbase[attrStr] += 2
#traitbase[attrEnd] += 2
#traitmax[attrStr] += 2
#traitmax[attrEnd] += 2

~ 6 is Maximum for Intelligence and Charisma
#traitmax[attrInt] = 6
#traitmax[attrCha] = 6

~max skill ranks is 4
perform hero.assign[Hero.SkillLimit4]

~immune to Radiation and Poison
perform hero.assign[Hero.RadImmune]
perform hero.assign[Hero.PoiImmune]</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stMisterHandy" name="Mister Handy Robot" description="You have 360° vision and improved sensory systems that can detect smells, chemicals, and radiation, reducing the difficulty of Perception tests that rely on sight and smell by 1. You are also immune to radiation and poison damage, but you cannot use chems, nor can you benefit from food, drink, or rest. You move by jet propulsion, hovering above the ground, unaffected by difficult terrain or obstacles. Your carry weight is 150 lbs., and it cannot be increased by your Strength or perks, but it can be increased by modified armor. You cannot recover from your own injuries or heal health points without receiving repairs (see Healing Robots, p.34).\n\nYou cannot manipulate the physical world like humans do, instead you have three of the arm attachments in the Arm Attachments table, determined by your choice of equipment pack. If you select an arm that features a weapon, you also gain 20 shots of ammo for that weapon." compset="OriginTrait">
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcMisterHandy"/>
    <eval phase="Initialize" priority="1000">perform hero.assign[Hero.RadImmune]
perform hero.assign[Hero.PoiImmune]</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="stUnitedStand" name="United We Stand" description="Trade caravan posts in your settlements attract traders every 5 days rather than 7. Settlements you establish, by any means, have a base Defense resource of 4. You gain either Energy Weapons or Small Guns as a bonus tag skill (your choice). Your Damage Resistance is increased by +1 while in cover, and you deal +1 CD damage while you and your companions are outnumbered." compset="OriginTrait" summary="You gain either Energy Weapons or Small Guns as a bonus tag skill. Your Damage Resistance is increased by +1 while in cover, and you deal +1 CD damage while you and your companions are outnumbered.">
    <usesource source="srcFalloutSettler"/>
    <tag group="OriginCat" tag="spcMinuteman"/>
    <eval phase="PreTraits" priority="1000"><![CDATA[perform hero.findchild[Origin].setfocus

doneif (state.isfocus = 0)

focus.field[orMaxTagSkills].value += 1

~additional tag skill must be one of Energy Weapons or Small Guns
focus.field[orSklChoiceExpr4].text = "component.Skill & !Skill.TagSkill & (thingid.skEnergyWpns|thingid.skSmallGuns)"]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="spcComMinuteman" name="Commonwealth Minuteman" description="“Protect the people at a minute’s notice.” A promise to live by, you belong to a unique brand of survivors in the Commonwealth who put others before themselves. With the threat of raiders, radioactive mutants, and morally corrupt factions that travel the wastes, another settlement always needs your help.\n\nYou could be a long-standing veteran of the Minutemen, rising to prominence in your defense of Diamond City against super mutant attackers. You could have signed on later, as the group’s founders tried to organize a government and unite settlements around the Commonwealth (only to be thwarted by the assassination of all the representatives in attendance), taking up residence in the old Fort Independence. “The Castle ‘’ could have been your home shortly before it was lost to a sea monster emerging from the Boston shoreline. Whatever your participation, the Quincy Massacre was a pivotal moment in your personal history, with Clint’s defection to the Gunners, Colonel Hollis’s capture and subsequent execution, and the Gunners slaughtering all but a few survivors in Quincy.\n\nPreston Garvey believed himself the only Minutemen survivor of the Quincy Massacre, but what if he was mistaken? What if you also survived, split off from your fellow militiamen, or went along with Clint’s plans just to live, but never losing the spirit of the Minutemen’s pledge to protect the citizens of the Commonwealth? Maybe you left the group before the events of Quincy, disenfranchised by the politics and infighting after the death of General Becker, but ready to dust off the hat and coat once more for someone who can reunite the militia and bring it back to its former glory." compset="Origin" uniqueness="unique">
    <usesource source="srcFalloutSettler"/>
    <tag group="HitLocation" tag="Head"/>
    <tag group="HitLocation" tag="Torso"/>
    <tag group="HitLocation" tag="ArmLeft"/>
    <tag group="HitLocation" tag="ArmRight"/>
